<h2>Traditional Māori Navigation Mathematics Unit</h2>
<p>Year 8 - Complete Assessment Framework</p>
</div>
<div class="info-box">
<h3>🎯 About This Rubric</h3>
<p>This master rubric provides comprehensive assessment criteria for all aspects of the Traditional Navigation Mathematics unit. It integrates:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Mathematical Skills:</strong> Calculations, problem-solving, geometric reasoning</li>
<li><strong>Cultural Understanding:</strong> Respect for mātauranga Māori and traditional knowledge</li>
<li><strong>NZ Curriculum Alignment:</strong> Level 4 Mathematics achievement objectives</li>
<li><strong>Holistic Assessment:</strong> Knowledge, skills, values, and cultural competency</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Mathematical Skills Assessment -->
<div class="category-header">🔢 Mathematical Skills &amp; Application</div>
<table class="rubric-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="width: 20%;">Criteria</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Excellent (4)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Good (3)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Satisfactory (2)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Needs Improvement (1)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Calculation Accuracy</strong><br/><em>(40% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">All calculations correct with clear, systematic working shown. Uses appropriate mathematical notation.</td>
<td class="level-good">Most calculations correct (80%+) with working shown. Minor errors in notation or process.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Some calculations correct (60-79%). Basic working shown but incomplete or unclear.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Few correct answers (&lt;60%). Limited or no working shown. Major calculation errors.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Problem-Solving</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Demonstrates sophisticated problem-solving strategies. Explains reasoning clearly. Checks answers for reasonableness.</td>
<td class="level-good">Uses appropriate problem-solving strategies. Explains most reasoning. Generally checks answers.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic problem-solving approach. Limited explanation of reasoning. Rarely checks answers.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Struggles with problem-solving. No clear strategy evident. Does not check answers.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Formula Application</strong><br/><em>(20% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Correctly selects and applies formulas (d=st, speed=d/t, etc.). Rearranges formulas appropriately. Understands when to use each.</td>
<td class="level-good">Usually selects correct formulas. Applies them correctly most of the time. Some confusion with rearrangement.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Sometimes selects correct formulas. Needs support with application. Limited understanding of rearrangement.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Rarely selects appropriate formulas. Cannot apply formulas independently. No understanding of rearrangement.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Geometric Reasoning</strong><br/><em>(10% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Demonstrates deep understanding of angles, circles, and directions. Can explain geometric concepts clearly.</td>
<td class="level-good">Good understanding of angles and circles. Can explain most geometric concepts adequately.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic understanding of geometric concepts. Limited ability to explain reasoning.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Weak understanding of geometric concepts. Cannot explain geometric reasoning.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<!-- Cultural Understanding Assessment -->
<div class="category-header">🏛️ Cultural Understanding &amp; Respect</div>
<table class="rubric-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="width: 20%;">Criteria</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Excellent (4)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Good (3)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Satisfactory (2)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Needs Improvement (1)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cultural Knowledge</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Demonstrates deep understanding of traditional navigation methods and their cultural significance. Makes meaningful connections between mathematics and culture.</td>
<td class="level-good">Good understanding of traditional navigation. Makes some connections between mathematics and culture.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic awareness of traditional navigation. Limited connections made between mathematics and culture.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Little understanding of cultural context. No meaningful connections made.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Te Reo Māori Use</strong><br/><em>(20% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Uses te reo Māori terms accurately and confidently. Demonstrates effort to pronounce correctly. Shows respect for the language.</td>
<td class="level-good">Uses most te reo terms correctly. Generally pronounces well. Shows basic respect for language.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Uses some te reo terms, not always accurately. Pronunciation needs work. Basic respect shown.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Rarely uses te reo terms. Poor pronunciation effort. Limited respect for language evident.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cultural Protocols</strong><br/><em>(25% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Consistently demonstrates respect for cultural protocols. Participates appropriately in karakia and cultural activities. Shows cultural sensitivity.</td>
<td class="level-good">Usually demonstrates respect for protocols. Participates in cultural activities. Generally culturally sensitive.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Sometimes demonstrates respect for protocols. Participates minimally. Needs reminders about cultural sensitivity.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Rarely demonstrates respect for protocols. Limited participation in cultural activities. Lacks cultural sensitivity.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Appreciation of Mātauranga Māori</strong><br/><em>(25% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Deeply values traditional knowledge. Recognizes sophistication of traditional mathematical systems. Makes connections to own learning.</td>
<td class="level-good">Values traditional knowledge. Recognizes some sophistication in traditional systems. Makes some connections.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic appreciation of traditional knowledge. Limited recognition of sophistication. Few connections made.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Little appreciation of traditional knowledge. Does not recognize sophistication of traditional systems.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<!-- Communication & Presentation -->
<div class="category-header">💬 Communication &amp; Presentation</div>
<table class="rubric-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="width: 20%;">Criteria</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Excellent (4)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Good (3)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Satisfactory (2)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Needs Improvement (1)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Mathematical Communication</strong><br/><em>(40% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Explains mathematical thinking clearly and precisely. Uses correct mathematical vocabulary. Diagrams and working are clear and well-organized.</td>
<td class="level-good">Explains mathematical thinking adequately. Uses most mathematical vocabulary correctly. Generally clear working shown.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic explanation of mathematical thinking. Limited use of mathematical vocabulary. Working sometimes unclear.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Cannot explain mathematical thinking clearly. Incorrect or no mathematical vocabulary. Working unclear or absent.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Written Expression</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Writing is clear, well-organized, and engaging. Complete sentences used. Spelling and grammar excellent.</td>
<td class="level-good">Writing is generally clear and organized. Mostly complete sentences. Few spelling/grammar errors.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Writing is basic but understandable. Incomplete sentences sometimes. Several spelling/grammar errors.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Writing unclear or disorganized. Many incomplete sentences. Frequent spelling/grammar errors.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Presentation Quality</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Work is neat, well-presented, and professional. Visual aids enhance understanding. Cultural elements respectfully incorporated.</td>
<td class="level-good">Work is neat and generally well-presented. Visual aids used appropriately. Cultural elements included.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Work is readable but basic presentation. Limited visual aids. Basic cultural elements included.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Work is messy or hard to read. No visual aids. Cultural elements absent or inappropriate.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<!-- Critical Thinking & Reflection -->
<div class="category-header">🧠 Critical Thinking &amp; Reflection</div>
<table class="rubric-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="width: 20%;">Criteria</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Excellent (4)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Good (3)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Satisfactory (2)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Needs Improvement (1)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Analysis &amp; Evaluation</strong><br/><em>(35% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Provides insightful analysis. Evaluates information critically. Makes sophisticated connections between concepts.</td>
<td class="level-good">Provides good analysis. Evaluates information adequately. Makes logical connections between concepts.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Provides basic analysis. Limited evaluation of information. Makes simple connections between concepts.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Limited analysis. No evaluation of information. Cannot make connections between concepts.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Self-Reflection</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Reflects deeply on learning. Identifies own strengths and areas for growth. Sets meaningful learning goals.</td>
<td class="level-good">Reflects on learning. Identifies some strengths and areas for growth. Sets appropriate learning goals.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic reflection on learning. Limited identification of strengths/weaknesses. Generic learning goals.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Minimal reflection. Cannot identify strengths/weaknesses. No meaningful learning goals set.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cultural Perspective</strong><br/><em>(35% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Demonstrates sophisticated understanding of how culture shapes knowledge systems. Compares and contrasts perspectives thoughtfully.</td>
<td class="level-good">Demonstrates good understanding of cultural perspectives on knowledge. Makes appropriate comparisons.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic awareness of cultural perspectives. Limited comparison of different approaches.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Little awareness of cultural perspectives. Cannot compare different approaches to knowledge.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<!-- Collaborative Learning -->
<div class="category-header">👥 Collaborative Learning &amp; Engagement</div>
<table class="rubric-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="width: 20%;">Criteria</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Excellent (4)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Good (3)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Satisfactory (2)</th>
<th style="width: 20%;">Needs Improvement (1)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Teamwork</strong><br/><em>(40% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Excellent collaborator. Contributes meaningfully. Listens to and respects others' ideas. Helps resolve conflicts constructively.</td>
<td class="level-good">Good collaborator. Makes solid contributions. Generally listens and respects others. Handles conflicts appropriately.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Basic collaborator. Makes some contributions. Sometimes listens to others. Needs support with conflict resolution.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Poor collaborator. Minimal contributions. Does not listen to others. Contributes to conflicts rather than resolving them.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cultural Respect in Groups</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Models cultural respect in all interactions. Ensures all voices are heard. Actively promotes inclusive learning environment.</td>
<td class="level-good">Shows cultural respect in interactions. Allows others to contribute. Supports inclusive environment.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Generally respectful in interactions. Sometimes dominates or withdraws. Basic support for inclusivity.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Limited respect in interactions. Dominates or withdraws excessively. Does not support inclusive environment.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Learning Engagement</strong><br/><em>(30% weighting)</em></td>
<td class="level-excellent">Consistently engaged and on-task. Shows genuine interest and curiosity. Seeks out additional learning opportunities.</td>
<td class="level-good">Usually engaged and on-task. Shows interest in learning. Participates in learning opportunities.</td>
<td class="level-satisfactory">Sometimes engaged. Interest varies. Participates when directly prompted.</td>
<td class="level-needs-improvement">Rarely engaged. Shows little interest. Minimal participation even when prompted.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
