<!-- Teacher Notes -->
<div class="no-print" style="background: #f0f8f4; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 8px; border: 2px solid #2C5F41;">
<h3>👩‍🏫 Implementation Notes for Teachers</h3>
<h4>Using This Rubric:</h4>
<ul class="criteria-list">
<li>Share rubric with students BEFORE beginning assessment tasks</li>
<li>Use rubric for both formative feedback and summative assessment</li>
<li>Consider self-assessment and peer-assessment using appropriate sections</li>
<li>Adapt criteria weightings based on specific learning objectives of each task</li>
</ul>
<h4>Cultural Assessment Considerations:</h4>
<ul class="criteria-list">
<li>Consult with cultural advisors about cultural understanding criteria</li>
<li>Consider inviting kaumātua to participate in cultural assessment</li>
<li>Balance Western assessment approaches with Māori assessment values (whanaungatanga, manaakitanga, kotahitanga)</li>
<li>Recognize that cultural understanding develops over time - allow for growth</li>
</ul>
<h4>Moderation Guidelines:</h4>
<ul class="criteria-list">
<li>Use exemplars to calibrate scoring across teachers</li>
<li>Conduct regular moderation meetings to ensure consistency</li>
<li>Document reasoning for borderline decisions</li>
<li>Seek second opinions on complex or borderline assessments</li>
</ul>
<h4>Providing Feedback:</h4>
<ul class="criteria-list">
<li>Give specific, actionable feedback for improvement</li>
<li>Highlight strengths as well as areas for growth</li>
<li>Include culturally responsive feedback (acknowledge cultural growth)</li>
<li>Provide opportunities for reassessment where appropriate</li>
</ul>
</div>
